### [Luke Chapter 12](../../../bib/kjv/luk012.htm#001.md)

[Luke 12:1](../../../bib/kjv/luk012.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_001">luk 12:1</span></span>

An innumerable multitude (τῶν μυριάδων τοῦ ὄχλου)

The word μυρίας strictly means a number of ten thousand. It is our word
myriad. Hence, generally, of any countless number.

First of all

Many connect this with what follows: "first of all beware," etc.

Leaven

See on [Mat 13:33](../../../bib/kjv/mat013.htm#033.md).

