[Luke 12:3](../../../bib/kjv/luk012.htm#003.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_003">luk 12:3</span></span>

Closets (ταμείοις)

The word has the same root as: τέμνω, to cut or divide, and means an
apartment where supplies are divided and apportioned: a treasury,
magazine, and therefore a secret and well-guarded place. There the
steward (ταμίας), the distributor, has his seat.

